{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"770380d2-8da6-42d8-b393-82f82d4d9b13","content":"The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. It can't help with post-mortem investigation.\n\nFor **analyzing** your `.dmp` file, here are your best options:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n   ```\n   Then use commands like `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, etc.\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core <your-file>.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** (Windows) — load the dump and use the SOS debugging extension.\n\n**Quick triage commands** once inside `dotnet-dump analyze`:\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `clrstack` — show managed call stack\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `dso` — dump stack objects\n\nWould you like help running any of these tools on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"20f12dc6-9caf-486c-82fb-b258278a9e73","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. Let me help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":381},"id":"b971c96d-354a-4d69-8206-be722b19713f","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:08:30.919Z","parentId":"dee58d7c-8f44-45f0-b6c6-23153672bb29"}
